Citation.sAbstract: Isobaric liquid-liquid equilibrium (ELL) data (tie lines and miscibility gaps) for the ternary system water + acetonitrile + limonene were determined at atmospheric pressure and at temperatures ranging from (296.15 +- 0.5) K to (323.15 +- 0.5) K. The reliability of the experimental tie-line data was ascertained by using two overall concentrations for each tie-line. The equilibrium data were correlated using NRTL and UNIQUAC equations to obtain new and previously unavailable UNIQUAC and NRTL interaction parameters. Experimental data were also compared with those predicted by UNIFAC group contribution method. At the studied temperatures, the UNIQUAC equation fitted the experimental data better than NTRL, with a root-mean square deviation value between 0.51 and 1.1 %. The miscibility gap disappears for an acetonitrile mass fraction equal to about 81% at 306.15 K.
Citation.sTitle: Liquid-Liquid Equilibrium for the Water + Acetonitrile + Limonene System at different temperatures
